[normal]AFS0105[bold]Written evidence submitted by the [bold]CBI Response[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]The government’s decentralisation agenda is the right one – increased freedoms for teachers and school leaders supports the improvem[bold]ent of standards and educational outcomes.[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]For the programme to be successful in the long[bold]-[bold]term, schools need clear guardrails within wh[bold]ich to work and deliver these improvements – and this includes [bold]strong governance and leadership, as well as s[bold]mart accountability sy[bold]stems[bold]. Not enough attention has yet been paid to these guardrails.[bold]&#xa0;
